messages.message:
So we have a map on the frontend called `orgMembersDict`

ex:
```{
    "sherif.elmetwally.1_instabase.com (http://sherif.elmetwally.1_instabase.com)": {
        "fullName": "Sherif Elmetwally",
        "privacyPolicy": "OPT_IN",
        "email": "<mailto:sherif.elmetwally+1@instabase.com|sherif.elmetwally+1@instabase.com>",
        "isVerified": true,
        "isActive": true,
        "isDisabled": false,
        "firstName": "Sherif",
        "lastName": "Elmetwally",
        "type": "USER",
        "found": true,
        "username": "sherif.elmetwally.1_instabase.com (http://sherif.elmetwally.1_instabase.com)",
        "principalType": "user",
        "principalTypeV2": "USER",
        "role": "admin",
        "rolesV2": {}
    }
}```
Where we can go from username -> user friendly name
Makes sense, do you know how we put that map together?
